node.text:
Here’s the truth about “FDA Approved”:

There’s a BIG misconception that the FDA diligently reviews and approves new ingredients before we start eating them. 

Sadly this isn’t the case. 

New ingredients are usually approved by the food manufacturer themselves, and NOT by the FDA. 

All an ingredient manufacturer has to do is HIRE THEIR OWN EXPERTS to claim it’s safe. This is the green light to start adding it to food products.

Several “FDA Approved” products have been yanked from the shelves after they were found to be downright dangerous. 

But this doesn’t happen overnight. 

History shows that it takes YEARS before the FDA acts and removes harmful products from the market. 

Something very serious needs to happen – like deaths – before the FDA takes action. And even then, they may not.

Remember how Johnson & Johnson’s talc powder was recently removed from the shelves after slews of cancer claims and cover-ups by the company?

Well, the FDA didn’t ban it. 

J&J voluntarily decided to stop selling it to stop lawsuits from piling up.

Meanwhile, this controversial ingredient is banned in Europe. 

This just goes to show how little the FDA has done to protect our health.

Even though we’ve made tremendous progress…the truth is that big companies just don’t change fast enough.

I believe we deserve to live in a world where our products can be made without weird – and nasty – ingredients.

Is that too much to ask?

Apparently so. Because we are so far away it’s crazy.

So, I decided to take matters into my own hands.

I launched @truvani and we have one main goal: eliminate nasty ingredients from all daily-use products.

We started with supplements. Now we are creating personal care products.

You’d think this was a parody...but somebody, somewhere, thought this was a great idea. Bribing someone into doing something that’s supposed to “protect” their health with something that clearly destroys it, has got to be the worst idea ever. Yet, I’d never put it past Big Food to let a marketing opportunity pass them by. 

Of course, no one thinks a Krispy Kreme donut is healthy. Their donuts are full of refined sugar - which alone is addictive, makes you fat, tired, depressed, age faster, makes your skin dull, weakens immunity and when consumed in excess causes all sorts of diseases.

And they also fill their donuts with other ingredients and man-made additives that are known to destroy the immune system and feed disease: 

❌ HYDROGENATED SOYBEAN OIL: This unhealthy oil is too high in omega-6 fatty acids and increases the risk of obesity, inflammation, cardiovascular disease, cancer, and autoimmune diseases.

❌ MONO AND DIGLYCERIDES: Contains trans fat which is strongly correlated with an increased risk of type 2 diabetes and heart disease.

❌ CALCIUM PROPIONATE: This preservative disrupts the metabolism and can promote weight gain. Animal studies show that it also leads to high blood sugar and insulin resistance, which increases the risk of type 2 diabetes.

❌ CELLULOSE GUM: This thickener is usually made from wood, because it’s cheap. Research links consumption of this additive (not naturally occurring when found in whole food) to weight gain, inflammation and digestive problems.

Krispy Kreme should be ashamed and not plastered all over the news as if they are doing us any favors. 

This is maddening because most people don’t know what is really in Krispy Kreme’s donuts and how they could affect their health.

Could you imagine the government regulating pizza?

Domino’s uses “Phase Oil” to grease their pans, which they call a “buttery-flavored oil”, but it’s actually artificially flavored hydrogenated soybean oil preserved with the controversial preservative TBHQ. 

⚠️ A peer-reviewed study by the Environmental Working Group found that TBHQ may harm the immune system.

⚠️ Eating a diet full of bleached flour, sugar, and soybean oil wreak havoc on healthy gut microbiome over time.

If you want to boost your immunity, start with your plate.

Health scares always make me think about my overall health and mortality. And it reminds me of why I got into eating better in the first place. 

My journey to real food all started with a hospital trip. Even though it was for something that was completely out of my control, it made me realize that I was ignoring my overall health.

Then, everything changed.

I started blogging about food and ingredients on Food Babe. I also launched my company @Truvani, where I sell remarkable supplements. 

And given this entire situation we’re in, I thought I would share some of the things I currently do each day to support my health:

⚡Drinking lemon water first thing in the morning - which helps the body flush toxins and provides a dose of vitamin C

⚡Sleeping for at least 8 hours each night by not staying up late surfing and reading all the bad news!

⚡Eat lots of fruits and vegetables - and make green smoothies and salads for lunch.

⚡ Avoiding refined sugar – I love eating golden berries (full of Vitamin C) instead of sugar-filled snacks to curb my sweet tooth.

⚡ Taking my immune-support supplements religiously (like Vitamin D, Vitamin C) 

⚡ Eating fermented foods and taking probiotics to promote good gut health and a healthy immune system.

⚡ Spending time outdoors with my family, taking long walks and playing at the park. In addition to getting regular exercise each morning. 

I hope you are staying sane and healthy in this trying time!

node.text:
It’s been years since I’ve bought conventional cooking oils like Mazola and Wesson. These oils are heavily processed, extracted with the neurotoxin hexane, and come from GMO crops that are treated with toxic pesticides and chemicals. 

You also don’t want to eat oils like soybean and “vegetable oil” often because they’re too high in omega-6 fatty acids, which increases the risk of obesity, inflammation, cardiovascular disease, cancer, and autoimmune diseases.

Try this instead:

🔥 COCONUT OIL – The tropical saturated fat in coconut oil is made up of medium-chain triglycerides (MCT), which is shown to reduce cholesterol and obesity. Virgin unrefined coconut oil withstands temperatures up to about 350 degrees, so it’s great for most baking and medium-high heat sauteing. 

🔥 EXTRA VIRGIN OLIVE OIL – There’s olive oil fraud going on, and some brands are mixed with unlabeled GMO oils (like soybean oil), so it’s important to find a brand you trust. I like Nuñez De Prado brand and use it to make my own salad dressings and other cold applications.

🔥 EXTRA VIRGIN SESAME OIL – Best for low-heat sauteing and works great when used sparingly as a condiment in stir-frys because it has a strong flavor. A naturally refined version is better for high-heat. 

🔥 GRASS-FED GHEE - This clarified butter doesn’t contain dairy proteins or sugars, so it works well for high heat cooking.

🔥 AVOCADO OIL is another option for high heat cooking.
